To open a Bootstrap toast on click of a button at the bottom right of the page, you can follow these steps:

1. First, include Bootstrap CSS and JavaScript files in your HTML document.
2. Create a button element for triggering the toast.
3. Create a toast element with the necessary classes for Bootstrap.
4. Use JavaScript to toggle the display of the toast when the button is clicked.

Here's an example code snippet:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Bootstrap Toast Example</title>
  <link href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
  <button id="toastButton" class="btn btn-primary">Show Toast</button>
</div>

<div class="toast" id="myToast" role="alert" aria-live="assertive" aria-atomic="true" data-delay="2000">
  <div class="toast-header">
    <strong class="mr-auto">Bootstrap Toast</strong>
    <button type="button" class="ml-2 mb-1 close" data-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close">
      <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
    </button>
  </div>
  <div class="toast-body">
    Hello, this is a Bootstrap toast!
  </div>
</div>

<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.5.1.slim.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@popperjs/core@2.5.4/dist/umd/popper.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

<script>
  $(document).ready(function(){
    $('#toastButton').click(function(){
      $('.toast').toast('show');
    });
  });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

This code will display a button "Show Toast" at the bottom right of the page. When clicked, it will trigger a Bootstrap toast to appear briefly with the message "Hello, this is a Bootstrap toast!".
